			<tr>
				<td><font face="verdana" size="1">
				<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/open.gif">&nbsp;<a href="/quests/default.asp">Quests</a><br>
				<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tline.gif">
				<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/open.gif">&nbsp;<a href="default.asp?land=2463">Rathe Mountains</a><br>
				<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tline3.gif">
				<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/open.gif">&nbsp;<b>Robe of the Lost Circle(Complete Info)</b><br><br>
				</td>
			</tr>
				
			<tr>
			<td>
				<p>
					<font face="verdana" size="3"><b>    Robe of the Lost Circle(Complete Info)</b>&nbsp;<a href="../Subscribe.asp?DID=412305"><font face="Verdana" size="2">[Subscribe to this document]</font></a></font>
					<br>
					<font face="verdana" size="2">
					<b><a href="mailto:cidvincent@angelfire.com">Descher Fisticuff</a> | 
		                        4/18/2001 4:27:42 PM</b></font></p>
					
					<p>
					<font face="verdana" size="2">I've combined all the info from the posts and have come up with a real quick summary and info on spawns and such:<BR>
<BR>
1st - You must earn your purple headband in Qeynos.  This can be easy or difficult.  First is the 4 gnoll pup scalps, gnolls are found in Qeynos hills and North Qeynos.  You get your white headband, then you must get 3 putrid rib bones, found on most putrid skeletons, closest to Qeynos residing at the skeleton ruins between Surefall Glade and BlackBurrow.  Turn in your white headband and the 3 rib bones, and get your second, yellow headband.  Yellow headband and the blackburrow gnoll pelts... unruined, and 1 skin.  Pelts are often found on elites, commanders and burlys.  Not as often found on guardsman... but can be attained that way.  Skins are found on Burly, elites*rarer*, and commanders. Turn 2 black burrow pelts and 1 skin and your yellow headband and achieve the 3rd sash, the orange headband.  This is the hardest part of the entire headband quest, respectively though, not the purple.  You have to gain 2 remains of fallen brothers, and also the head of Ghanex Drah.  Ghanex Drah is the easiest as he has no place holder, and is a fairly easy necro at around level 25 solo... not completely sure about that, but I was able to take him.  The other remains is the skull of brother Shren.  Now, I found this while wondering on the southeast wall.  Near the shadowknights, just wandering, not completely sure of the place holder, but I was told it was a shadow wolf.  (Now to shorten some time, kill the shadow wolf and try to get a shadow pelt :P)  The other is the head of dareb.  This is found also a named gnoll. All around 20-25'ish.  They are NOT nodrop but are lore.  You can probably pick em up for 100p considering they are a rather boring 1 hour camp at most.  The one that drops the head of dareb can be wandering just off of spires.  Neither despawn very quickly.  Now take the 2 heads, skull, and orange headband back to Phin, and achieve the 4th headband, Red Headband.  This one is a bit hard in one aspect, camping High priestess Zaharn.  She spawns in Permafrost, in the king room, dropping Zaharns Coronet, without a rare.  The other item, skull of j'hentra can be found in SK or in Lake Rathe off of embalmers near the SK zone.  I found my Skull of J'hentra on an embalmer, but I heard a certain shaman, name slipping me currently, drops it, although I have no witnessed this.  Dagger of Marnek is the 3rd item, found in Befallen, an old Monk monastery, on the third floor.  Found on a Thurmagist, who is a female Erudite... Not just Necro Thurmagist, but The Thurmagist.  Shes a necro, easily solo'd at 30.  You will be returning to this room to retrieve Blackened Wand, who is dropped by Priest Amiaz, who spawns in the same room as her.  Watch out cause all the necros will cast compact on them while you fight.<BR>
<BR>
After getting those items, bring them back to qeynos, give them to phin along with your red headband, and get your fifth and final headband, the purple headband.  There is no blue... but there is a black, that can be found on Brother QWinn and Zephyl for sure, although I have never fought Lu'Sun.  <BR>
<BR>
Also, you will want to earn your freeport sash of order.  I believe first is bone chips, snake scales, rat fang, and low level items like that, easy way to find out is hailing a guildmaster who distributes them.  Second is not too difficult.  One catch, Legonnaire Bracers DO NOT DROP IN EC anymore.  You can spend days there, and will not see one.  Only place is CrushBone, where they drop off about every Orc Legonnaire. The third quest requires other items, trantuala chitin, derv ring and GLS and prior sash... I believe.  The 4th is blackened wand.  I'm not exactely sure, cause it is a bit... confusing.  I myself had a friend, run in and kill the guildmasters :P.  2 in the front are around level 30.  Not too hard, but guards to help.  They drop red sash of order and newbie tunic.  <BR>
<BR>
Other items you will need is Jonathans Whistling Warsong, 4p or so song from Bard guilds in Freeport or Qeynos.  Easy to attain.<BR>
<BR>
Another item is Shadow Silk.  You will need tailoring skill in this, but I made it with 2 skill in tailoring, with luck.  I think the minimum is 20, although not sure.  You need a shadow wolf pelt from shadow wolves in SK or from Nektulos, East commons, Misty Thicket.... or whereever else you find Shadow wolves.  Not too rare, but can be bought from other people for like 10p.  You need Gather Shadows, a necro invis spell... like a 4 gold spell or so.  Found in most necro guilds. Also a swatch of silk.  Made by combining 2 spider silks, not spiderling silks.  Now, combine swatch of shadow silk, gather shadows and shadow wolf pelt and you will get Shadow Silk.<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
Now, you have to attain Code of Zan Fi.  This is found in Solusek Ro Dungeon B, or Nagafens Lair, SolB... soldungb.  He spawns in the king room, on the throne, which the king does not :P.  30 minute spawn time, PH is normally a greater kobold, not just greater kobold.  I don't think ive seen anything else spawn there.  Sure, hes not too rare, but ive seen people camp him for hours.  I've seen him within 20 minutes of getting into the group*No idea how long they'd been there*. Code of Zan Fi is ALL/ALL Primary secondary 2 str 1 weight.  Looks like a book.  Take that book, and your purple headband to South Karana and look for Brother QWinn.  Qwinn walks fast.  Ask someone to hail him still while you run to find him.<BR>
Return the code and the purpleheadband and you will reciever a nice chunk of exp, 2 blue bubbles at level 30, and needle of the void, all/all .1 weight looks like chipped bone rod.<BR>
<BR>
Now here the best part of all. Raster of Guk.<BR>
<BR>
I have camped him for about 10~ hours total, At 4 hour consecutive.  Others were at 2 hour or so  periods.  Raster drops Idol of Zan Fi.  3 str 3 wisdom, looks like that orc divine aura item.  1 weight, all/all.  Many people on my server now call Raster a myth*hehe* even though we know he exists.  He spawns outside of the elder minotaur pit.  He is on Live frog faction, and his PH is a greater minotaur or a frog itself.  Its normally the only mino that doesn't move, and he is next to the firepot that does not have a flame in it.  Theres a bunch of steps infront of him, if that helps.  He spawns every 20 or so minutes.  But the best method I have heard of is the 2 kill, 1 spawn method.  You kill the placeholder twice in a row, and then wait for the third to despawn.  This is for the people who plan on spending a lot of time on him.  Instead of the 2.6 spawns per human hour, you will get 3.  A whole .4 more chances to get him.  Which adds up after multiple hours.  Once you get his Idol, lucky, Take the Idol of Zan Fi and your red sash of order to Brother Zephyl, he has a PH of Haste and a really black lookin drake named somethin drake... I believe Obsidian.  Hes not too hard, drops NODROP Drakescales for another quest I am not aware of.  I had a friend who camped Zephyl, longer then they camped Raster for.  Although I heard Zephyl was pretty common.  Give him both and you will get Rare Robe Pattern.<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
Now take Needle of the Void, Jonathans Whistling War Song, Shadow Silk and Rare robe pattern into a Large sewing Kit.  You DO NOT need skill in tailoring to do this *Thanks Verant*.  So you can craft it easily.  Everything in this quest are not nodrop except for Code, Idol, Needle and RAre Robe Pattern.  So you can buy yourself most quest items.  Code of Zan Fi is easy to FD outside of king, and loot it.  Idol is a little harder, you will need a group 35+ and about 45 to solo effectively, while well equipped. <BR>
<BR>
Get your Robe and be happy, cause you're gonna have to get rid of it for Robe of the Whistling Fists, and once you get attachted to that robe... Boom, its gone for a stupid book :P You will have to use it for your Celestial Fists.  Which thanks to spoilers, can be achieved in a day or so after you get your Robe of the Whistling fists with the correct guild.  And about 18 of em.  Though I aint gonna go into a lot of detail about the epic, cause I havent completed it.<BR>
<BR>
Well good luck hope this is compiled well.
			<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</font></p>
					</p>
			</td>
			</tr>
